cmSecurityMIB.name: cmSecurityMIB

revisions.description: Notes from release 201606140000Z (1) added cmSecurityUserRemoteCryptoUser to cmSecurityUserTable Notes from release 201602080000Z (1)Added literal netconf to CmSecurityPrivLevel Notes from release 201509180000Z (1)Added cmSecurityCryptoPassword attribute to cmSecurityUserTable Note from release 201106270000Z, (1)Added f3TacacsPrivLevelControlEnabled, f3TacacsDefaultPrivLevel Note from release 201104140000Z, (1)Added cmSecurityUserAction to support remove-lockout Note from release 201101050000Z, (1)Added f3UsmUserTable - an augment to UsmUserTable Note from release 201002120000Z, (1)MIBs updated for supported functionality in R4.3CC and R4.1CM (a)cmRemoteAuthServerTable has new objects cmRemoteAuthServerAccountingPort to support RADIUS accounting Notes from release 200903190000Z, (1)MIB version ready for release FSP150CC GE101, GE206 devices (a)Added Textual convention CmSecurityPolicyStrength (b)Added MIB scalar cmSecurityPolicyStrength (2)Following changes are made to the cmSecurityUserTable, (a)cmSecurityUserPassword column to modify security user password (b)cmSecurityUserStorageType and cmSecurityUserRowStatus columns added thereby allowing creation/deletion of Security Users (c)cmSecurityUserComment, cmSecurityUserPrivLevel, cmSecurityUserLoginTimeout, cmSecurityUserNumFailedLoginAttempts, cmSecurityUserCliPagingEnable columns are now read-write to allow write access. Notes from release 200803030000Z, (1)MIB version ready for release FSP150CM 3.1.

cmSecurityMIB.contactinfo: Raghav Trivedi ADVA Optical Networking, Inc. Tel: +1 972 759-1239 E-mail: rtrivedi@advaoptical.com Postal: 2301 N. Greenville Ave. #300 Richardson, TX USA 75082
cmSecurityMIB.description: This module defines the Security MIB definitions used by the F3 (FSP150CM/CC) product lines. These are used to manage the user/authentication for CLI/GUI sessions. Copyright (C) ADVA Optical Networking.

CmRemoteAuthProtocol.name: CmRemoteAuthProtocol
CmRemoteAuthProtocol.description: Enumerations for remote authentication protocol. none - No remote authentication protocol, radius - RADIUS (Remote Authentication Dial-In User Service), tacacs - TACACS+(Terminal Access Controller Access Control System).

CmSecurityAccessOrder.name: CmSecurityAccessOrder
CmSecurityAccessOrder.description: Enumerations for order for security access. local - Local database for user/security validation, remote - Remote protocol for user/security validation.

CmSecurityAuthType.name: CmSecurityAuthType
CmSecurityAuthType.description: Enumerations for remote authentication protocol types. pap - Password Authentication Protocol, chap - Challenge-Handshake Authentication Protocol.

CmSecurityPrivLevel.name: CmSecurityPrivLevel
CmSecurityPrivLevel.description: Enumerations for Security Privilege Level. retrieve - Retrieve Privilege Level (can only VIEW management information), maintenance - Maintenance Privilege Level (can VIEW management, as well as perform maintenance operations such as loopbacks, etherjack diagnosis etc.) provisioning - Provisioning Privilege Level (can perform Provisioning operations) superuser - Super User Privilege Level (can perform all operations) testuser - Retrieve Privilege Level and some maintenance, provisioning operations. cryptouser - Crypto User Privilege Level (can perform security operations) netconf - NETCONF Privilege Level

CmRemoteAuthOrder.name: CmRemoteAuthOrder
CmRemoteAuthOrder.description: Enumerations for order for remote authentication access. first - first to access the remote authentication, second - second to access the remote authentication, third - third to access the remote authentication.

CmSecurityPolicyStrength.name: CmSecurityPolicyStrength
CmSecurityPolicyStrength.description: Enumerations for security policy strength low - Low Security Policy, medium - Medium Security Policy, high - High Security Policy.

UsmUserAccessType.name: UsmUserAccessType
UsmUserAccessType.description: Enumerations for type of USM User read-only - Read only, read-write - Read write , trap-only - Trap Only.

SecurityUserAction.name: SecurityUserAction
SecurityUserAction.description: Provides ability to manage security users.

SnmpSecurityTrapType.name: SnmpSecurityTrapType
SnmpSecurityTrapType.description: Provides ability to manage security traps. all - trap is reported when user logs in, logs out or is locked out loginFailed - trap is reported only when user failed to log in disabled - security traps are disabled.

cmAccessOrder.name: cmAccessOrder
cmAccessOrder.description: Order of access for security, i.e. try 'local' first or 'remote' first.

cmAuthType.name: cmAuthType
cmAuthType.description: In case of remote authentication, the chosen protocol.

cmNASIpAddress.name: cmNASIpAddress
cmNASIpAddress.description: In case of remote authentication RADIUS, the Network Access Server's IP Address.

cmSecurityPolicyStrength.name: cmSecurityPolicyStrength
cmSecurityPolicyStrength.description: This object represents the security policy strength of the system. Based on this value, the system puts additional restrictions on the user id and password rules.

cmRemoteAuthServerAccountingEnabled.name: cmRemoteAuthServerAccountingEnabled
cmRemoteAuthServerAccountingEnabled.description: This object allows to enable/disable RADIUS Accounting on all authentication servers.

f3TacacsPrivLevelControlEnabled.name: f3TacacsPrivLevelControlEnabled
f3TacacsPrivLevelControlEnabled.description: This object allows to enable/disable the use of ENABLE authorization control to determine the Privilege Level configured by the remote authentication server. This object is only valid for TACACS+. Default value of this object is TRUE.

f3TacacsDefaultPrivLevel.name: f3TacacsDefaultPrivLevel
f3TacacsDefaultPrivLevel.description: This object allows specification of the default privilege level of the TACACS+ user, when the use of ENABLE authorization control is DISABLED, i.e. f3TacacsPrivLevelControlEnabled is set to FALSE.

f3NasIpv6Addr.name: f3NasIpv6Addr
f3NasIpv6Addr.description: This object describe the ipv6 address.

f3SecurityTrapType.name: f3SecurityTrapType
f3SecurityTrapType.description: This object provides ability to manage whether report security trap.

f3SecurityTrapInfo.name: f3SecurityTrapInfo
f3SecurityTrapInfo.description: This object is used to describe the security trap info. This object is used only in trap and GET operation on this object will return empty string.

f3UserPrivMgmtControl.name: f3UserPrivMgmtControl
f3UserPrivMgmtControl.description: This object is used to enable/disable User Privilege Management.

f3UserPrivRspTimeout.name: f3UserPrivRspTimeout
f3UserPrivRspTimeout.description: This object is used to set response timeout for user privilege upgrade request in minutes.

cmSecurityUserTable.name: cmSecurityUserTable
cmSecurityUserTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to the security users. Entries cannot be created in this table by management application action.

cmSecurityUserEntry.name: cmSecurityUserEntry
cmSecurityUserEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular security user.

cmSecurityUserNumFailedLoginAttempts.name: cmSecurityUserNumFailedLoginAttempts
cmSecurityUserNumFailedLoginAttempts.description: Security User Number of Failed Login Attempts.

cmSecurityUserLockedout.name: cmSecurityUserLockedout
cmSecurityUserLockedout.description: Whether the security user has been locked out.

cmSecurityUserLastLockedoutTime.name: cmSecurityUserLastLockedoutTime
cmSecurityUserLastLockedoutTime.description: Security User Last Locked out Time.

cmSecurityUserCliPagingEnable.name: cmSecurityUserCliPagingEnable
cmSecurityUserCliPagingEnable.description: Whether the security user has CLI paging enabled.

cmSecurityUserRemoteUser.name: cmSecurityUserRemoteUser
cmSecurityUserRemoteUser.description: Whether the security user is a remote user.

cmSecurityUserPassword.name: cmSecurityUserPassword
cmSecurityUserPassword.description: Password of the security user. Note that this attribute is a SET only attribute.

cmSecurityUserStorageType.name: cmSecurityUserStorageType
cmSecurityUserStorageType.description: The type of storage configured for this entry.

cmSecurityUserRowStatus.name: cmSecurityUserRowStatus
cmSecurityUserRowStatus.description: The status of this row. An entry MUST NOT exist in the active state unless all objects in the entry have an appropriate value, as described in the description clause for each writable object. The values of cmSecurityUserRowStatus supported are createAndGo(4) and destroy(6). All mandatory attributes must be specified in a single SNMP SET request with cmSecurityUserRowStatus value as createAndGo(4). Upon successful row creation, this object has a value of active(1). The cmSecurityUserRowStatus object may be modified if the associated instance of this object is equal to active(1).

cmSecurityUserAction.name: cmSecurityUserAction
cmSecurityUserAction.description: This object provides ability to perform specific actions on security user. remove-lockout - this removes the locked out condition on the security user .

cmSecurityCryptoPassword.name: cmSecurityCryptoPassword
cmSecurityCryptoPassword.description: Second level password used in connectguard configurations. This applies only to crypto users. Note that this attribute is a SET only attribute.

cmSecurityUserRemoteCryptoUser.name: cmSecurityUserRemoteCryptoUser
cmSecurityUserRemoteCryptoUser.description: Indicates if a security user is a remote crypto user.

cmRemoteAuthServerTable.name: cmRemoteAuthServerTable
cmRemoteAuthServerTable.description: A list of entries corresponding to the remote authentication servers. Entries cannot be created in this table by management application action.

cmRemoteAuthServerEntry.name: cmRemoteAuthServerEntry
cmRemoteAuthServerEntry.description: An entry containing information applicable to a particular remote authentication server.

cmRemoteAuthServerIndex.name: cmRemoteAuthServerIndex
cmRemoteAuthServerIndex.description: Unique index to address/configure a specific Remote Authentication Server.

cmRemoteAuthServerEnabled.name: cmRemoteAuthServerEnabled
cmRemoteAuthServerEnabled.description: This object allows enabling/disabling a Remote Authentication Server.

cmRemoteAuthServerOrder.name: cmRemoteAuthServerOrder
cmRemoteAuthServerOrder.description: This object determines the order in which the Remote Authentication Servers are accessed for security information.

cmRemoteAuthServerIpAddress.name: cmRemoteAuthServerIpAddress
cmRemoteAuthServerIpAddress.description: This object allows to specify an IP Address for the Remote Authentication Server.

cmRemoteAuthServerPort.name: cmRemoteAuthServerPort
cmRemoteAuthServerPort.description: This object allows to specify a Port for Remote Authentication Server.

cmRemoteAuthServerNumRetries.name: cmRemoteAuthServerNumRetries
cmRemoteAuthServerNumRetries.description: This object allows to specify the number of retries the Remote Authentication Server must be tried for security access before giving up.

cmRemoteAuthServerTimeout.name: cmRemoteAuthServerTimeout
cmRemoteAuthServerTimeout.description: This object allows to specify the timeout period for timing out a security access request to the Remote Authentication Server.

cmRemoteAuthServerSecret.name: cmRemoteAuthServerSecret
cmRemoteAuthServerSecret.description: This allows configuration of secret password for Remote Authentication Server request.

cmRemoteAuthServerAccountingPort.name: cmRemoteAuthServerAccountingPort
cmRemoteAuthServerAccountingPort.description: This object allows to specify a Port for RADIUS Accounting.

cmRemoteAuthServerIpVersion.name: cmRemoteAuthServerIpVersion
cmRemoteAuthServerIpVersion.description: This object describe the Ip Version.

cmRemoteAuthServerIpv6Addr.name: cmRemoteAuthServerIpv6Addr
cmRemoteAuthServerIpv6Addr.description: This object describe the Ipv6 Address.

f3UsmUserTable.name: f3UsmUserTable
f3UsmUserTable.description: This table is the extension of the F3 USM User Table.

f3UsmUserEntry.name: f3UsmUserEntry
f3UsmUserEntry.description: An entry in the F3 USM User Table.

f3UsmUserAccessType.name: f3UsmUserAccessType
f3UsmUserAccessType.description: This indicates the type of USM User, read-only, read-write, trap-only.

f3PrivilegeChangeTable.name: f3PrivilegeChangeTable
f3PrivilegeChangeTable.description: This table is used for Restricted User Login via NMS. This is for users with lower privileges to elevate them to higher ones for limited amount of time.

f3PrivilegeChangeUserName.name: f3PrivilegeChangeUserName
f3PrivilegeChangeUserName.description: The name string for user authentication purposes

f3PrivilegeChangeIpv4Address.name: f3PrivilegeChangeIpv4Address
f3PrivilegeChangeIpv4Address.description: IPv4 address of interface to which user's terminal is connected.

f3PrivilegeChangeIpv6Address.name: f3PrivilegeChangeIpv6Address
f3PrivilegeChangeIpv6Address.description: IPv6 address of interface to which user's terminal is connected.

f3PrivilegeChangeTerminalIpv4Address.name: f3PrivilegeChangeTerminalIpv4Address
f3PrivilegeChangeTerminalIpv4Address.description: Source IPv4 address of connected terminal.

f3PrivilegeChangeTerminalIpv6Address.name: f3PrivilegeChangeTerminalIpv6Address
f3PrivilegeChangeTerminalIpv6Address.description: Source IPv6 address of connected terminal.

f3PrivilegeChangeCurrentPrivilege.name: f3PrivilegeChangeCurrentPrivilege
f3PrivilegeChangeCurrentPrivilege.description: Current privilege level of the user, who is requesting role upgrade.

f3PrivilegeChangeRequestedPrivilege.name: f3PrivilegeChangeRequestedPrivilege
f3PrivilegeChangeRequestedPrivilege.description: Privilege requested by user for session.

f3PrivilegeChangeDuration.name: f3PrivilegeChangeDuration
f3PrivilegeChangeDuration.description: Requested time period by user (in minutes).

f3PrivilegeChangeRemainingTime.name: f3PrivilegeChangeRemainingTime
f3PrivilegeChangeRemainingTime.description: Time remaining in session with upgrade user privilege (in seconds).

f3PrivilegeChangeRemoteName.name: f3PrivilegeChangeRemoteName
f3PrivilegeChangeRemoteName.description: The name string for Radius/Tacacs authentication purposes.

f3SecurityTrap.name: f3SecurityTrap
f3SecurityTrap.description: This is security trap. Security traps are reported according to value of f3SecurityTrapType object.

f3PrivilegeChangeTrap.name: f3PrivilegeChangeTrap
f3PrivilegeChangeTrap.description: This trap is sent every time a privilege change request is changed (added, modified, removed).

cmSecurityCompliance.name: cmSecurityCompliance
cmSecurityCompliance.description: Describes the requirements for conformance to the CM Security group.

cmSecurityObjectGroup.name: cmSecurityObjectGroup
cmSecurityObjectGroup.description: A collection of objects used to manage the CM Security group.

cmSecurityNotifGroup.name: cmSecurityNotifGroup
cmSecurityNotifGroup.description: A collection of notifications used in the CM Security group.
